# Cursor rules for SoulCap

Read `AGENTS.md` (repo root) before writing any code — it has the full architecture, conventions,
recipes, and ship workflow. `ROADMAP.md` has build-ready specs for what to do next. These rules
are the short, non-negotiable version.

## The product
SoulCap is a calm, private, **offline-first** PWA. A personalised emotional operating system —
NOT an AI therapist, mood tracker, or crisis service. Success = the user needs the app less.

## Never
- Never add a network call: no `fetch`, `XMLHttpRequest`, CDN `<script>`, web-font link, or
  analytics. The shipped app in `docs/` makes ZERO network requests after load. No dependencies.
- Never claim it is therapy / treats / diagnoses / replaces care. Never mark a technique as
  clinically reviewed (none are).
- Never add crisis phone numbers or a country/region picker (removed by owner). Help is
  gentle, number-free, country-agnostic guidance only.
- Never add streaks, points, badges, guilt notifications, red counts, infinite scroll, fake
  typing indicators, or "I care about you" copy.
- Never contact anyone on the user's behalf — "Message someone" opens the user's own `sms:`.
- Never write ES6+ in `docs/` (no arrow fns, `let/const`, classes, template literals, optional
  chaining). Plain `var`/`function`, ES5-safe, no transpile.

## Always
- Product code = `docs/` only (`index.html`, `app.css`, `data.js`, `app.js`, `sw.js`).
  `backend/` and `mobile/` are un-deployed labs — don't wire them into the PWA.
- Build DOM with the `el()` helper; put user-visible content in `data.js`; style via CSS tokens
  in `app.css` (theme-aware: light default, dark, night). Never hardcode colours.
- After a state change call `save()` then `render()` (or `reRender()` to keep scroll position).
- Keep the safety keyword lists in `docs/app.js` (`CRISIS_HARD` etc) in sync with
  `backend/src/ai/safety/safety-gate.service.ts`.
- Honour `prefers-reduced-motion`; keep body copy ≥15px; allow compact 9–14.5px iPhone
 labels/metadata only with strong contrast and browser zoom; keep touch targets ≥48px;
 one filled accent button per screen.
- Safety-critical behaviour MUST get a Playwright test in `e2e/` (it gates the deploy).

## Ship workflow (every change that touches `docs/`)
1. Bump `CACHE` in `docs/sw.js`, `swCache`+`version` in `VERSION.json`, `APP_VERSION`+`version`
   in `docs/app.js` — all matching (e.g. `soulcap-v072` / `0.7.2`).
2. Update `CHANGELOG.md`; bump version in `SAFETY.md` + `HANDOVER.md`.
3. `npx playwright test` — all green (mobile + desktop, Chromium).
4. Commit + push to `main`. CI (`.github/workflows/deploy.yml`) gates the Pages deploy on the tests.

## Done-gate
Reduces stress? Calming? Simple? Private? Honest about limits? Accessible? Won't overwhelm someone
mid-panic? Has a test if safety-critical? Would Apple ship it? If not — not done.
